oc:kn_1386d12d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recalc.py reports #VALUE! errors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "#VALUE! errors occur when wrong data types enter calculations (text instead of number). Solution: verify all inputs are formatted as numbers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mixed data types in formula chains propagate errors throughout the model." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_328ba23b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When validating DCF model outputs for reasonableness" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Terminal value must not exceed 80% of enterprise value. Terminal growth rate must be less than WACC. Terminal growth should not exceed risk-free rate or long-term GDP growth." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Terminal value >80% of EV indicates over-reliance on perpetuity assumptions. Terminal growth ≥ WACC creates infinite value, which is mathematically invalid." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_522315d8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, before building or rebuilding DCF model sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before writing DCF formulas, define ALL section row positions and headers first. Test formulas immediately after creation to catch reference errors early." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The most common error source is writing formulas before finalizing layout, causing #REF! errors when headers are inserted later." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8cf5ff16 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When DCF valuation produces unreasonably high implied share price" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If implied price is far too high: check terminal value isn't >80% of EV, verify terminal growth < WACC, review if growth assumptions are realistic, consider if margins are too optimistic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overvaluation typically stems from overly aggressive terminal assumptions or unrealistic margin expansion projections." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_92160306 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When case selector is not working properly" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If consolidation column not updating when switching scenarios: verify case selector cell contains 1, 2, or 3; check INDEX/OFFSET formulas reference correct row range and selector cell; ensure absolute references ($B$6) are used for selector; test by manually changing selector cell." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Scenario switching requires absolute cell references and correct INDEX/OFFSET ranges; relative references or wrong ranges prevent proper case selection." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a9eeaf16 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After building or modifying a DCF model, before delivery" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run recalc.py and validate all formulas produce zero errors. Then spot-check: (1) one FCF formula references correct assumption rows, (2) case selector updates consolidation column, (3) revenue formulas reference consolidation column not nested IFs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Spot-checking catches the top 5 DCF errors: formula row references off, missing cell comments, simplified sensitivity tables, wrong scenario block references, and missing borders." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_dbeff11c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When DCF valuation produces unreasonably low implied share price" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If implied price is far too low: verify net debt vs net cash is correct, check if WACC is too high, review if projections are too conservative, consider if terminal growth is too low." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Undervaluation typically results from excessive discount rates, incorrect net debt/cash treatment, or overly pessimistic projections." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ddf05b9a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recalc.py reports #DIV/0! errors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "#DIV/0! errors result from division by zero or empty cells. Fix by wrapping divisions in IF statements: =IF([Divisor]=0,0,[Numerator]/[Divisor])." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unprotected division operations fail when projected values are zero, especially in early projection years or edge-case scenarios." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f4734794 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recalc.py reports #REF! errors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "#REF! errors in DCF models are caused by formulas referencing wrong rows after headers were inserted. Solution: rebuild with correct row references or start over with proper layout planning. Prevention: define all row positions BEFORE writing formulas." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Row insertion shifts cell references, breaking formula integrity. This is the #1 most common DCF model error." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:req_2dd7372e a oc:RequirementKnowledge ;
    oc:isOptional false ;
    oc:requirementValue "DCF valuation methodology and common Excel error types" .

oc:req_444dc93a a oc:RequirementKnowledge ;
    oc:isOptional false ;
